      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ALFIE'S POP (2) proved too good on debut over 400m at this track to score by 2.25 lengths (23.17). Drawn to be prominent early. Expected to go close again. BARKLEY LANE (1) was game in defeat off a low draw at the latest outing, finishing third and beaten 1.5 lengths (20.17) behind Lumeah Matilda at Gunnedah. Winning chance. WONKY KEY DONKEY (3) had been racing in honest fashion recording three placings in a row before finishing fifth (23.43) at this track latest. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings five times from six starts. Expected to run well. KEY JASPER (7) is building a nice sequence of placings – hard to fault that form.",
